# Day 1

## Activities
Today, I participated in several activities focused on artificial intelligence (AI) and biology. We discussed the ethical use of AI, explored how AI is used to solve real-world problems, and learned about the different types of AI.
Later, we completed a hands-on DNA extraction lab and analyzed elephant DNA to identify genetic relationships and understand how DNA can be used in scientific research and wildlife conservation.

## What I Learned
Today, I learned that AI can be a powerful tool when it is used responsibly and ethically. 
I gained a better understanding of the different types of AI and how they are applied in fields such as healthcare, education, engineering, and everyday technology. 
I also learned how scientists extract DNA from cells and use DNA analysis to determine relationships between elephant populations. This showed me how genetics plays an important role in conservation and biological research.

## My Favorite Part
My favorite part of the day was the DNA extraction activity because it gave me the opportunity to perform a real scientific experiment. 
I also enjoyed learning how scientists use elephant DNA to study family relationships and help protect endangered species. 
It was exciting to connect what we learned in class to real-world scientific research.
